##  ** Jump into the world of SEO! **

Are you looking to advance your experience in the world of digital marketing?
Ready to start a fulfilling career that will fast-track your exposure to all
aspects of SEO - including technical, content, and user experience?

Reload Media has an opportunity for someone who is passionate about SEO,
genuinely loves to work within a team, and strives to exceed clients’
expectations. You will be surrounded by a supportive team of 50+ expert
digital marketers and have access to the best training and digital
opportunities that only a leading agency can provide!

_ This is the role for you if: _

  * You want to be hands-on working on SEO and content campaigns while working collaboratively with your team and clients 
  * You thrive juggling multiple projects and are confident to work across a range of different tasks 
  * You like to think creatively but back up your decisions with data 
  * You enjoy being in control of your own work and coming up with the strategy and execution 
  * Most importantly, you are excited to make your mark in a leading digital marketing agency by delivering high performing campaigns for our clients 

This position is well suited to a recent marketing graduate or someone with
around 12 months' hands-on marketing experience who is looking to build a
career specialising in Search Engine Optimisation. In return, you'll receive
extensive training across all areas of digital marketing, while working in a
supportive and fun agency environment. We invest heavily in the professional
development of all Reloaders, creating 'individualised careers' and building
the skills of talented marketers.

##  ** What You’ll Be Doing **  

In this role, you'll be responsible for the SEO strategy for a range of
clients, which will include things like:

  * Working in a small team of 6-8 people (known internally at Reload as a ‘Pod’) to assist with the coordination and implementation of digital marketing projects & campaigns. 
  * Undertaking ongoing keyword research & developing the keyword strategy 
  * Content ideation and creation as part of digital marketing and SEO campaigns 
  * Continuously review and optimise the on-site content and improve your clients’ websites to deliver the best results to your clients 
  * Undertaking website reviews, briefing web developers and completing competitor research. 
  * Review Google Analytics, website sales, and performance data to pull campaign insights 
  * Prepare monthly/quarterly reports with insights and recommendations in DataStudio, PowerPoint, and other reporting tools 
  * Be actively involved in meetings and discussions to plan campaigns, compare results and provide insights and expertise 
  * Build strong relationships with clients through regular communication and meetings 
  * Deliver exceptional customer service to both clients and teammates. This means meeting deadlines, being proactive, and being flexible in your delivery. 

##  ** Who We’re Looking For **

  * A tertiary qualification (or similar) in a relevant field. I.e. advertising, marketing, business, communication, etc. 
  * A good understanding of digital marketing fundamentals 
  * You are someone who thrives in the numbers – you enjoy working in excel, know a formula or two, and would describe yourself as an analytical mind 
  * Excellent written communication with the ability to write copy in various formats as well as brief copywriters and review content 
  * You are someone who is at ease, juggling multiple clients, and effective in managing your workload to hit deadlines. 
  * You are someone who is confident to solve problems themselves and doesn't stop until they get to the solution 
  * You are someone who is naturally curious and likes to experiment with different ideas and find new ways of delivering great results 
  * You are someone who gets genuine enjoyment from working with people and are comfortable talking to and meeting with clients from day one 

##  ** Nice to Have Skills **

While not essential for the role, a mix of the below skills will be looked
upon favorably and allow you to hit the ground running.

  * Hands-on experience executing SEO tasks 
  * Experience with eCommerce platforms, digital content, CMS platforms 
  * Experiences with Google Analytics and reporting 
  * Experience with tracking (Analytics tags, GTM, pixels, etc.) 

##  ** Benefits & Salary **

We're super proud that Reload's stand-out culture and happy team have resulted
in us being named as one of the ** Top 10 Best Places to Work in the Media &
Marketing industry for 2023! **

Aside from the usual perks of working in an agency, a core pillar of what
defines Reload is a focus on 'People & Careers'. Developing individuals and
providing opportunities for growth is at the core of our business model. To
support this, you’ll have your own professional development budget, access to
our industry leading training and our learning and development platform. We
also believe that 'Attitude Creates Ability', and that means at Reload we
focus on the way you approach work, not just the skills you have. This is the
stuff that really excites us and we hope it does you too!

_ Some of the other benefits we provide are: _

  * 2 additional Rest & Relaxation days per year & 1 day of birthday leave 
  * Flexible hours and hybrid working options 
  * Opportunities for domestic & international travel 
  * Additional menstrual & menopausal leave 
  * Phone and call plan 
  * Regular events & parties 
  * Paid volunteer day each year   

  * Paid blood donation leave 
  * Free counselling, for professional or personal matters   

  * 3 months paid parental leave on top of statutory parental leave 

Take a look at our careers page on our website to find out all about the perks
and benefits of working at Reload.

The salary range for this role is $50,000 to $60,000 plus Superannuation,
based on experience.  

##  ** What Life At Reload Has To Offer You **

Reload Media is a leading digital marketing agency in Brisbane, with clients
across multiple continents. At Reload, you'll be working with some of
Australia's (and the world's) leading brands including Yamaha, Terry White
Chemmart, Aje, The Lodge Bar, Henne, Gelatissimo, and more.

As part of the wider Reload Group, you’ll also enjoy the benefits of being
part of a global agency, with offices in Brisbane, London, and Manila. Unlike
most other agencies of our size, we are backed by 80+ people in our
international offices, with Reload able to say that we are 'truly global'.

At Reload you can expect to join a collaborative, energetic, and supportive
team. A huge amount of passion and energy goes into creating an inspiring and
fun environment that sets you up to thrive, with many Reloaders creating
impressive careers for themselves - part of why we were awarded as one of the
** Top 10 Places to Work in Australia in Media/Marketing for 2023! **

